1. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper deals with the application of a parallel-in-time integration scheme for the solution of a hyperbolic flow problem, which involves the spatial discretization of a partial differential equation by a finite difference method. This falls under the domain of numerical analysis, making cs.NA the most likely sub-category. 

2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on the use of parallel-in-time integration schemes to increase the amount of parallelism, which is a requirement arising from the rapidly growing number of CPUs in high performance computer systems. This makes cs.DC a likely sub-category. 

3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper deals with the solution of a hyperbolic flow problem, which is often used as a test case for integration schemes for numerical weather prediction (NWP). This falls under the domain of computational science and engineering, making cs.CE a likely sub-category. 

4. cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the implementation of integration schemes already widely used in NWP (RK-3, partially split forward Euler, forward–backward). This makes cs.MS a possible sub-category.
